function spawn_close_pid(pid: <link xref="GLib.Pid">GLib.Pid</link>): void {
    // Gjs wrapper for g_spawn_close_pid()
}
  </code></synopsis>
  <p>On some platforms, notably Windows, the <link xref="GLib.Pid"/> type represents a resource
which must be closed to prevent resource leaking. <link xref="GLib.spawn_close_pid"/>
is provided for this purpose. It should be used on all platforms, even
though it doesn't do anything under UNIX.</p>

